        <detaileddescription>
<para>The buf just contains the funcid on the src element that is ready to receive the returned data. Also we are returning the data along the <ref refid="classMsg" kindref="compound">Msg</ref> that brought in the request, so we don&apos;t need to scan through all Msgs in the <ref refid="classElement" kindref="compound">Element</ref> to find the right one. So we bypass the usual SrcFinfo::sendTo, and instead go right to the Qinfo::addToQ to send off data. Finally, the data is copied back-and-forth about 3 times. Wasteful, but the &apos;get&apos; function is not to be heavily used. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
