    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This specialized <ref refid="classOpFunc" kindref="compound">OpFunc</ref> is for looking up a single field value using a single argument. It generates an opFunc that takes two arguments:<orderedlist>
<listitem><para>FuncId of the function on the object that requested the value.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Index or other identifier to do the look up. The <ref refid="classOpFunc" kindref="compound">OpFunc</ref> then sends back a message with the info. Here T is the class that owns the function. A is the return type L is the lookup index. </para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
